\i \cf0 Many crema recipes call for a bit more of the active culture to be added to the cream in order to encourage rapid thickening.\'a0 Using a mere two teaspoons will still thicken the cream considerably and the 24 hour slow culturing process will encourage more complex flavor development.\'a0 Using buttermilk will lend the finished crema a slightly nutty flavor and a beautiful texture that is perfect for drizzling on just about anything.\'a0 Using more than 2 teaspoons of the active culture will simply produce a thicker final product.\'a0 Once the cream has thickened, feel free to add any flavor components that interest you.\'a0 I will sometimes add a bit of lime juice, salt, chile or even ground cumin depending upon its eventual application. Covered and refrigerated, the crema will keep for about 10 days or so.
